Fills in three Phase 8 MVP deferrals identified in the parity plan.

Per-session timeout watchdog:
- New asyncio task per spawned session (cancelled on session done)
- Mirrors TS bridgeMain.ts:1177-1192 / 1677-1692
- --session-timeout SECONDS now actually fires; the timer kills the
  child and marks the session in timed_out_sessions so the done-log
  distinguishes timeout from clean exit
- Shutdown cancels all pending timer tasks before SIGTERM

Two-track exponential backoff:
- New _BackoffTrack dataclass + two instances (conn_track, general_track)
- is_connection_error()-routed: TCP/TLS/DNS failures → conn track;
  everything else → general track
- Each track: initial_ms → doubles per failure (capped at cap_ms),
  give-up after give_up_ms wall-clock from first failure
- Successful poll resets BOTH tracks
- Give-up raises BridgeHeadlessPermanentError with the track name
- Mirrors TS bridgeMain.ts:1269-1399

Heartbeat mode (non-exclusive):
- When poll_config.non_exclusive_heartbeat_interval_ms > 0, at-capacity
  loop heartbeats each active work item (api.heartbeat_work) at the
  heartbeat interval instead of the at-cap poll interval
- Disabled by default (=0 in DEFAULT_POLL_CONFIG)
- Mirrors TS bridgeMain.ts:649-730

8 new regression tests:
- test_session_timeout_kills_session — armed timer fires
- test_session_timeout_disabled_when_unset — no timer when ms=None
- test_two_track_backoff_doubles_on_repeated_errors — flaky API
- test_backoff_track_gives_up_after_threshold — permanent failure
- test_general_track_used_for_non_connection_errors — routing
- test_successful_poll_resets_backoff_tracks — reset semantics
- test_heartbeat_mode_fires_when_at_capacity — beat count ≥ 2
- test_heartbeat_disabled_when_interval_zero — no beats at default

42/42 bridge_main tests pass; 592/592 bridge tests pass overall.

